std::vector<std::vector<AstLiteral*> > souffle::formNegatedLiterals ( AstProgram &  program,
AstAtom *  atom 
)

Forms the bodies that will replace the negation of a given inlined atom.

E.g. a(x) <- (a11(x), a12(x)) ; (a21(x), a22(x)) => !a(x) <- (!a11(x), !a21(x)) ; (!a11(x), !a22(x)) ; ... Essentially, produce every combination (m_1 ^ m_2 ^ ...) where m_i is the negation of a literal in the ith rule of a.

885  newClause->addToBody(std::unique_ptr<AstLiteral>(lit->clone()));
886  }
887 
888  versions.push_back(newClause);
889  }
890  }
891 
892  // Only perform one stage of inlining at a time.
893  // If the head atoms did not need inlining, try inlining atoms nested in the body.
894  if (!changed) {
895  std::vector<AstLiteral*> bodyLiterals = clause.getBodyLiterals();
896  for (size_t i = 0; i < bodyLiterals.size(); i++) {
897  AstLiteral* currLit = bodyLiterals[i];
898 
899  // Three possible cases when trying to inline a literal:
900  // 1) The literal itself may be directly inlined. In this case, the atom can be replaced
901  // with multiple different bodies, as the inlined atom may have several rules.
902  // 2) Otherwise, the literal itself may not need to be inlined, but a subnode (e.g. an argument)
903  // may need to be inlined. In this case, an altered literal must replace the original.
904  // Again, several possible versions may exist, as the inlined relation may have several rules.
905  // 3) The literal does not depend on any inlined relations, and so does not need to be changed.
906  NullableVector<std::vector<AstLiteral*>> litVersions = getInlinedLiteral(program, currLit);
907 
908  if (litVersions.isValid()) {
909  // Case 1 and 2: Inlining has occurred!
910  changed = true;
911 
912  // The literal may be replaced with several different bodies.
913  // Create a new clause for each possible version.
914  std::vector<std::vector<AstLiteral*>> bodyVersions = litVersions.getVector();
915 
916  // Create the base clause with the current literal removed
917  auto baseClause = std::unique_ptr<AstClause>(clause.cloneHead());
918  for (AstLiteral* oldLit : bodyLiterals) {
919  if (currLit != oldLit) {
920  baseClause->addToBody(std::unique_ptr<AstLiteral>(oldLit->clone()));
921  }
922  }
923 
924  for (std::vector<AstLiteral*> body : bodyVersions) {
925  AstClause* replacementClause = baseClause->clone();
926 
927  // Add in the current set of literals replacing the inlined literal
928  // In Case 2, each body contains exactly one literal
929  for (AstLiteral* newLit : body) {
930  replacementClause->addToBody(std::unique_ptr<AstLiteral>(newLit));
931  }
932 
933  versions.push_back(replacementClause);
934  }
935  }
936 
937  // Only replace at most one literal per iteration
938  if (changed) {
939  break;
940  }
941  }
942  }
943 
944  if (!changed) {
945  // Case 3: No inlining changes, so a clone of the original should be returned
946  std::vector<AstClause*> ret;
947  ret.push_back(clause.clone());
948  return ret;
949  } else {
950  // Inlining changes, so return the replacement clauses.
951  return versions;
952  }
953 }

Here is the call graph for this function:

NullableVector< std::vector< AstLiteral * > > souffle::getInlinedLiteral ( AstProgram &  program,
AstLiteral *  lit 
)

Tries to perform a single step of inlining on the given literal.

Returns a pair of nullable vectors (v, w) such that:

  • v is valid if and only if the literal can be directly inlined, whereby it contains the bodies that replace it
  • if v is not valid, then w is valid if and only if the literal cannot be inlined directly, but contains a subargument that can be. In this case, it will contain the versions that will replace it.
  • If both are invalid, then no more inlining can occur on this literal and we are done.

sips_t souffle::getSipsFunction ( const std::string &  sipsChosen)

Returns a SIPS function based on the SIPS option provided.

The SIPS function will return the index of the appropriate atom in a clause given a goal.

E.g. the 'max-bound' SIPS function will return the atom in the clause with the maximum number of bound arguments.

341  std::cerr << e.what() << std::endl;
342  exit(1);
343  }
344 
345  // ------ start souffle -------------
346 
347  std::string souffleExecutable = which(argv[0]);
348 
349  if (souffleExecutable.empty()) {
350  throw std::runtime_error("failed to determine souffle executable path");
351  }
352 
353  /* Create the pipe to establish a communication between cpp and souffle */
354  std::string cmd = ::which("mcpp");
355 
356  if (!isExecutable(cmd)) {
357  throw std::runtime_error("failed to locate mcpp pre-processor");
358  }
359 
360  cmd += " -e utf8 -W0 " + Global::config().get("include-dir");
361  if (Global::config().has("macro")) {
362  cmd += " " + Global::config().get("macro");
363  }
364  cmd += " " + Global::config().get("");
365  FILE* in = popen(cmd.c_str(), "r");
366 
367  /* Time taking for parsing */
368  auto parser_start = std::chrono::high_resolution_clock::now();
369 
370  // ------- parse program -------------
371 
372  // parse file
373  SymbolTable symTab;
374  ErrorReport errReport(Global::config().has("no-warn"));
375  DebugReport debugReport;
376  std::unique_ptr<AstTranslationUnit> astTranslationUnit =
377  ParserDriver::parseTranslationUnit("<stdin>", in, symTab, errReport, debugReport);
378 
379  // close input pipe
380  int preprocessor_status = pclose(in);
381  if (preprocessor_status == -1) {
382  perror(nullptr);
383  throw std::runtime_error("failed to close pre-processor pipe");
384  }
385 
386  /* Report run-time of the parser if verbose flag is set */
387  if (Global::config().has("verbose")) {
388  auto parser_end = std::chrono::high_resolution_clock::now();
389  std::cout << "Parse Time: " << std::chrono::duration<double>(parser_end - parser_start).count()
390  << "sec\n";
391  }
392 
393  // ------- check for parse errors -------------
394  if (astTranslationUnit->getErrorReport().getNumErrors() != 0) {
395  std::cerr << astTranslationUnit->getErrorReport();
396  std::cerr << std::to_string(astTranslationUnit->getErrorReport().getNumErrors()) +
397  " errors generated, evaluation aborted"
398  << std::endl;
399  exit(1);
400  }
401 
402  // ------- rewriting / optimizations -------------
403 
404  /* set up additional global options based on pragma declaratives */
405  (std::make_unique<AstPragmaChecker>())->apply(*astTranslationUnit);
406 
407  /* construct the transformation pipeline */
408 
409  // Magic-Set pipeline
410  auto magicPipeline = std::make_unique<ConditionalTransformer>(Global::config().has("magic-transform"),
411  std::make_unique<PipelineTransformer>(std::make_unique<NormaliseConstraintsTransformer>(),
412  std::make_unique<MagicSetTransformer>(), std::make_unique<ResolveAliasesTransformer>(),
413  std::make_unique<RemoveRelationCopiesTransformer>(),
414  std::make_unique<RemoveEmptyRelationsTransformer>(),
415  std::make_unique<RemoveRedundantRelationsTransformer>()));
416 
417  // Equivalence pipeline
418  auto equivalencePipeline =
419  std::make_unique<PipelineTransformer>(std::make_unique<MinimiseProgramTransformer>(),
420  std::make_unique<RemoveRelationCopiesTransformer>(),
421  std::make_unique<RemoveEmptyRelationsTransformer>(),
422  std::make_unique<RemoveRedundantRelationsTransformer>());
423 
424 #ifdef USE_PROVENANCE
425  // Provenance pipeline
426  auto provenancePipeline = std::make_unique<PipelineTransformer>(std::make_unique<ConditionalTransformer>(
427  Global::config().has("provenance"), std::make_unique<ProvenanceTransformer>()));
428 #else
429  auto provenancePipeline = std::make_unique<PipelineTransformer>();
430 #endif
431 
432  // Main pipeline
433  auto pipeline = std::make_unique<PipelineTransformer>(std::make_unique<AstComponentChecker>(),
434  std::make_unique<ComponentInstantiationTransformer>(),
435  std::make_unique<UniqueAggregationVariablesTransformer>(), std::make_unique<AstSemanticChecker>(),
436  std::make_unique<RemoveTypecastsTransformer>(),
437  std::make_unique<RemoveBooleanConstraintsTransformer>(),
438  std::make_unique<ResolveAliasesTransformer>(), std::make_unique<MinimiseProgramTransformer>(),
439  std::make_unique<InlineRelationsTransformer>(), std::make_unique<ResolveAliasesTransformer>(),
440  std::make_unique<RemoveRedundantRelationsTransformer>(),
441  std::make_unique<RemoveRelationCopiesTransformer>(),
442  std::make_unique<RemoveEmptyRelationsTransformer>(),
443  std::make_unique<ReplaceSingletonVariablesTransformer>(),
444  std::make_unique<FixpointTransformer>(
445  std::make_unique<PipelineTransformer>(std::make_unique<ReduceExistentialsTransformer>(),
446  std::make_unique<RemoveRedundantRelationsTransformer>())),
447  std::make_unique<RemoveRelationCopiesTransformer>(),
448  std::make_unique<PartitionBodyLiteralsTransformer>(),
449  std::make_unique<MinimiseProgramTransformer>(),
450  std::make_unique<RemoveRelationCopiesTransformer>(),
451  std::make_unique<ReorderLiteralsTransformer>(),
452  std::make_unique<MaterializeAggregationQueriesTransformer>(),
453  std::make_unique<RemoveEmptyRelationsTransformer>(),
454  std::make_unique<ReorderLiteralsTransformer>(), std::move(magicPipeline),
455  std::make_unique<AstExecutionPlanChecker>(), std::move(provenancePipeline));
456 
457  // Disable unwanted transformations
458  if (Global::config().has("disable-transformers")) {
459  std::vector<std::string> givenTransformers =
460  splitString(Global::config().get("disable-transformers"), ',');
461  pipeline->disableTransformers(
462  std::set<std::string>(givenTransformers.begin(), givenTransformers.end()));
463  }
464 
465  // Set up the debug report if necessary
466  if (!Global::config().get("debug-report").empty()) {
467  auto parser_end = std::chrono::high_resolution_clock::now();
468  std::string runtimeStr =
469  "(" + std::to_string(std::chrono::duration<double>(parser_end - parser_start).count()) + "s)";
470  DebugReporter::generateDebugReport(*astTranslationUnit, "Parsing", "After Parsing " + runtimeStr);
471 
472  pipeline->setDebugReport();
473  }
474 
475  // Toggle pipeline verbosity
476  pipeline->setVerbosity(Global::config().has("verbose"));
477 
478  // Apply all the transformations
479  pipeline->apply(*astTranslationUnit);
480 
481  // ------- execution -------------
482 
483  /* translate AST to RAM */
484  std::unique_ptr<RamTranslationUnit> ramTranslationUnit =
485  AstTranslator().translateUnit(*astTranslationUnit);
486 
487  std::vector<std::unique_ptr<RamTransformer>> ramTransforms;
488  ramTransforms.push_back(std::make_unique<ExpandFilterTransformer>());
489  ramTransforms.push_back(std::make_unique<HoistConditionsTransformer>());
490  ramTransforms.push_back(std::make_unique<MakeIndexTransformer>());
491  ramTransforms.push_back(std::make_unique<IfConversionTransformer>());
492  ramTransforms.push_back(std::make_unique<ChoiceConversionTransformer>());
493 
494  for (const auto& transform : ramTransforms) {
495  /* If the ram transform changed the program, show this */
496  if (transform->apply(*ramTranslationUnit)) {
497  std::stringstream ramProgStr;
498  ramProgStr << *ramTranslationUnit->getProgram();
499  ramTranslationUnit->getDebugReport().addSection(DebugReporter::getCodeSection(
500  transform->getName(), "RAM Program after " + transform->getName(), ramProgStr.str()));
501 
502  } else {
503  ramTranslationUnit->getDebugReport().addSection(DebugReportSection(
504  transform->getName(), "After " + transform->getName() + " " + " (unchanged)", {}, ""));
505  }
506  /* Abort evaluation of the program if errors were encountered */
507  if (ramTranslationUnit->getErrorReport().getNumErrors() != 0) {
508  std::cerr << ramTranslationUnit->getErrorReport();
509  std::cerr << std::to_string(ramTranslationUnit->getErrorReport().getNumErrors()) +
510  " errors generated, evaluation aborted"
511  << std::endl;
512  exit(1);
513  }
514  }
515  if (ramTranslationUnit->getErrorReport().getNumIssues() != 0) {
516  std::cerr << ramTranslationUnit->getErrorReport();
517  }
518 
519  if (!ramTranslationUnit->getProgram()->getMain()) {
520  return 0;
521  };
522 
523  if (!Global::config().has("compile") && !Global::config().has("dl-program") &&
524  !Global::config().has("generate")) {
525  // ------- interpreter -------------
526 
527  // configure interpreter
528  std::unique_ptr<Interpreter> interpreter;
529  if (!Global::config().has("interpreter")) {
530  interpreter = std::make_unique<LVM>(*ramTranslationUnit);
531  } else {
532  if (Global::config().get("interpreter") == "RAMI") {
533  interpreter = std::make_unique<RAMI>(*ramTranslationUnit);
534  } else {
535  interpreter = std::make_unique<LVM>(*ramTranslationUnit);
536  }
537  }
538 
539  std::thread profiler;
540  // Start up profiler if needed
541  if (Global::config().has("live-profile") && !Global::config().has("compile")) {
542  profiler = std::thread([]() { profile::Tui().runProf(); });
543  }
544  // execute translation unit
545  interpreter->executeMain();
546 
547  // If the profiler was started, join back here once it exits.
548  if (profiler.joinable()) {
549  profiler.join();
550  }
551 
552 #ifdef USE_PROVENANCE
553  // only run explain interface if interpreted
554  if (Global::config().has("provenance")) {
555  // construct SouffleProgram from env
556  InterpreterProgInterface interface(*interpreter);
557  if (Global::config().get("provenance") == "explain") {
558  explain(interface, true, false);
559  } else if (Global::config().get("provenance") == "explore") {
560  explain(interface, true, true);
561  }
562  }
563 #endif
564 
565  } else {
566  // ------- compiler -------------
567 
568  std::string compileCmd = ::findTool("souffle-compile", souffleExecutable, ".");
569  /* Fail if a souffle-compile executable is not found */
570  if (!isExecutable(compileCmd)) {
571  throw std::runtime_error("failed to locate souffle-compile");
572  }
573  compileCmd += " ";
574 
575  std::unique_ptr<Synthesiser> synthesiser = std::make_unique<Synthesiser>(*ramTranslationUnit);
576 
577  try {
578  // Find the base filename for code generation and execution
579  std::string baseFilename;
580  if (Global::config().has("dl-program")) {
581  baseFilename = Global::config().get("dl-program");
582  } else if (Global::config().has("generate")) {
583  baseFilename = Global::config().get("generate");
584  // trim .cpp extension if it exists
585  if (baseFilename.size() >= 4 && baseFilename.substr(baseFilename.size() - 4) == ".cpp") {
586  baseFilename = baseFilename.substr(0, baseFilename.size() - 4);
587  }
588  } else {
589  baseFilename = tempFile();
590  }
591  if (baseName(baseFilename) == "/" || baseName(baseFilename) == ".") {
592  baseFilename = tempFile();
593  }
594 
595  std::string baseIdentifier = identifier(simpleName(baseFilename));
596  std::string sourceFilename = baseFilename + ".cpp";
597 
598  bool withSharedLibrary;
599  std::ofstream os(sourceFilename);
600  synthesiser->generateCode(os, baseIdentifier, withSharedLibrary);
601  os.close();
602 
603  if (withSharedLibrary) {
604  compileCmd += "-s ";
605  }
606 
607  if (Global::config().has("compile")) {
608  auto start = std::chrono::high_resolution_clock::now();
609  compileToBinary(compileCmd, sourceFilename);
610  /* Report overall run-time in verbose mode */
611  if (Global::config().has("verbose")) {
612  auto end = std::chrono::high_resolution_clock::now();
613  std::cout << "Compilation Time: " << std::chrono::duration<double>(end - start).count()
614  << "sec\n";
615  }

617  if (!Global::config().has("dl-program")) {
618  executeBinary(baseFilename
619 #ifdef USE_MPI
620  ,
621  ((int)astTranslationUnit->getAnalysis<SCCGraph>()->getNumberOfSCCs()) + 1
622 #endif
623  );
624  }
625  }
626  } catch (std::exception& e) {
627  std::cerr << e.what() << std::endl;
628  std::exit(1);
629  }
630  }
631 
632 // finalize mpi, this is necessary for the symbol table
633 #ifdef USE_MPI
634  mpi::finalize();
635 #endif
636 
637  /* Report overall run-time in verbose mode */
638  if (Global::config().has("verbose")) {
639  auto souffle_end = std::chrono::high_resolution_clock::now();
640  std::cout << "Total Time: " << std::chrono::duration<double>(souffle_end - souffle_start).count()
641  << "sec\n";
642  }
643 
644  return 0;
645 }
